description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following four stories:

  • I Had a Date With Doom!
  • I Was Marooned on an Iceberg!
  • I Shoot with a Camera!
  • I Jumped from Eight Miles Up!

I Had a Date With Doom

When Joe, a pitcher for the Yankees, is told he has a deadly disease that gives him only 6 months left to live his entire life changes. With a new look on life and how short it truly is Joe begins to drastically change how he lives day to day, becoming a hero in the process. Will Joe's heroics grant him fame before his 6 month deadline or is he about to check out early?

I Was Marooned on an Iceberg

David Marston winds up stranded on an iceberg in the frigid waters of the Arctic. Without food or supplies he realizes it's only a short period of time before he's claimed by the freezing winds and creeping starvation; however, he'll learn that he isn't the only one on this iceberg and he just might become food for it's other inhabitants!

I Shoot with a Camera

Mister Marlin recounts his various "hunting" trips around the world, armed not with a high caliber rifle, but with a camera.

I Jumped from Eight Miles Up

Spike Murphy comes from a line of heroic jumpers; his father jumped out of planes during WWI; however, when Spike attempts an jump from eight miles up he may not survive.
name: I Jumped From Eight Miles Up!
